The Department shall use the Community Right-to-Know Fund for:
The collection, management, and analysis of data received by the Department from an owner or operator of a facility that is required by the federal Act or any regulations adopted under the federal Act to provide information to the State under § 7-602(b) of this subtitle;
Enforcement by the State of this subtitle or the federal Act;
Planning and training functions performed by the State or local instrumentalities as may be required by the federal Act including:
Conducting:
Incident response activities;
Shelter in place and evacuation planning;
Railroad, maritime, and transportation exercises; and
Emergency response activities;
The collection of hazardous material commodity flow information;
The acquisition and maintenance of chemical reference materials;
Public outreach activities including case studies, school safety, and emergency planning for citizens; and
Participation by emergency response personnel in related training conferences on local, State, and federal regulatory and compliance updates, incident command, and crisis control; and
Emergency response activities of the Department.

section.section:
The following persons and entities are exempt from paying any fees under this section:
Governmental agencies;
Farmers whose principal residence is located on their farm;
Charitable organizations as defined under § 6-101(d) of the Business Regulation Article;
Petroleum retail facilities with less than 75,000 gallons of gasoline and less than 100,000 gallons of diesel or similar fuel; and
Entities that are exempt from reporting under the federal Act.
